    		<h1 class="main-title">Rules</h1>

            <p class="main-content"> 1. Registering your details means that your Number goes into the pool of Numbers from which a random Numbers is chosen when there is a draw. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 2. You must be over 18 to play. If you are under 18 please ask an adult to play on your behalf. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 3. Only Numbers that are registered by players will be drawn. So, there is always at least one eligible winner. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 4. If the winner(s) fail to visit the site and collect then the prize pot is rolled into the next one. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 5. Players can only register once. You can only have one Number and one email registered at one time. Anyone found breaking this rule will have their entry disabled without notice. </p> 

            <p class="main-content"> 6. Once the draw has been made, those who have already registered the drawn Numbers are eligible to 'Collect'. Registering a Number after it has been drawn does not entitle you to collect for that draw. </p> 

            <p class="main-content"> 7. To 'Collect' the player needs to visit the site and press the 'Collect' button before the next draw. This only appears if you are a winner. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 8. Once a player has collected they have secured a proportion of the prize Airtime . The proportion they finally get depends on how many others from the winning Numbers collect before the next draw. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 9. Whenever there is a draw, those who have won and collected for the last draw will be notified of their winnings via email. </p> 

            <p class="main-content"> 10. By 'Player' we mean someone who lives is fortunate enough to have home with a Number and email address. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 11. Email reminders are provided to help you remember. If they fail, or your email provider chooses to filter them into Spam/Junk folders then we are not liable for missed winnings. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 12. In order to keep the site fair we reserve the right to query certain entries. In particular, 'role' based email addresses (eg. info@company.com) or non-personal addresses (eg. company@hotmail.com) are likely to be queried if they are one of multiple entries from a single postcode. We ask that you avoid using such email addresses if you can. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 13. We reserve the right to withold winnings if we cannot ascertain that the entry is legitimate. We may require proof of address. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 14. In order to reduce unwanted, and unopened emails, we will automatically cancel your daily draw alerts if you have not visited the site for over a month. </p>

            <p class="main-content"> 15. We may temporarily remove entries that have not visited the site for several months. These entries will be reactivated the next time the user logs in either directly on the site, or via a reminder email. </p>

